---
import SAGPLayout from "../../../layouts/SAGPLayout.astro";
import PageHero from "../../../components/PageHero.astro";
---

<SAGPLayout title="Membership Workspace | SAGP Executive Portal">

<PageHero
  kicker="Executive Portal"
  title="Membership Workspace"
  subtitle="Members, renewals, and audiences for Society communications."
  image="/assets/images/parthenon_night.jpg"
/>

<section class="section">
  <div class="workspace-grid">
    <article class="card feature-card">
      <h3>Membership Engine</h3>
      <p>
        The SAGP Membership Engine is currently a standalone desktop workspace
        for viewing members, updating membership records, and generating
        communication audiences.
      </p>
      <div class="callout">
        Phase I integration keeps the validated membership tool intact while
        exposing it through the Executive Portal as the Membership Workspace.
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h3>Members</h3>
      <p>
        Search and review canonical membership records, including names,
        affiliations, email addresses, regions, and membership status.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h3>Renewals</h3>
      <p>
        Update a member's last paid year and membership status when renewal
        information is received.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h3>Audiences</h3>
      <p>
        Generate email audiences such as current paid members, renewal reminder
        groups, expired members, and Executive and Board members.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section two-col">
  <div>
    <h2>Current workflow</h2>
  </div>

  <div>
    <ol>
      <li>Open the standalone SAGP Membership Manager.</li>
      <li>Choose an audience preset.</li>
      <li>Preview the matching members.</li>
      <li>Copy comma-separated email addresses for use in an email client.</li>
      <li>Optionally export the audience as CSV.</li>
    </ol>

    <p class="muted">
      Future versions may embed this workflow directly inside the Executive
      Portal. For now, the Membership Engine remains a validated standalone
      subsystem.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

</SAGPLayout>

<style>
.workspace-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
  gap: 24px;
}

.feature-card {
  grid-column: 1 / -1;
}

@media (max-width: 800px) {
  .workspace-grid {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  }
}
</style>
